        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">In answer to your original post, I believe it did say chance originally as well.</P><P>And in response to Reckim, I really have to agree with what he is saying. The chance to perma-charm something is just too good to be true. Pick an undead zone. Solo it means almost unlimited, and almost risk free XP, with a pet hasted 65%. A group of 3 necros with perma-pets hasted at 65% means they breeze through the whole zone and go camp Bloodpoints and Heliot Skull Helms while watching TV. As far as I know, there are critters in Fear that can be charmed. A group of 6 necros could pretty much have a picnic up there. </P><P>I love the abilty, I want the skill, but there is just too much room for abuse, and no necro to my knowledge even has it yet. And in answer to your enivitable question, yes I have read the skill listing. I am sure pallies read the listing on thier silence type spell when Luclin was released, and look at how fast that got nuked. </P><P>If anything, I would expect it to be down-graded to a long, but fixed duration charm, I would guess about 10 to 15 minutes. With a 72 minute refresh it is still not unbalancing. Personally, I will not be wasting a lot of effort drooling over this skill until it is out there and has seen active use for a bit, and if it remains un-nerfed, then maybe I will salivate a bit harder.</P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
